# Big LAZ tiles, rasterized outputs, and ad-hoc comparison reports.
# Regenerable from the upstream APIs — no reason to bloat the repo. The
# scripts create these directories at runtime via mkdir(parents=True),
# so they don't need to exist in the tree.
#
# Note: the root-level .gitignore also excludes `output/`, which applies
# here too. This local rule is defensive belt-and-suspenders.
output/*
results/*

# Ground-truth files are optional and often contain client-identifying
# addresses and tape-measure survey numbers. Keep them out of the repo
# by default; commit individual files explicitly if safe.
ground_truth/*.json
!ground_truth/.gitkeep
